                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 20, 1950, George F. Kennan, Counselor of the Department of State,
                    completed a 79-page memorandum on the international control of atomic energy.
                    This study treated the interrelated problems of international control, the
                    development of thermonuclear weapons, and national strategic plans. For extracts
                    from the Kennan memorandum and written comments on it by several officers of the
                    Department, see <ref target="#pg_22">pages 22</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
